title <size:18>Payment Gateway System (Annotated for Interview)</size>\n<size:11>Trace: "Merchant creates payment of Rs 500. User selects UPI. Gateway authorizes via Razorpay, captures payment, notifies merchant via webhook."</size>


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 1: FACADE — PaymentGateway
' ====================================================================
class PaymentGateway <<Facade>> {
    - paymentProcessor : PaymentProcessor
    - merchantRegistry : MerchantRegistry
    - ledger : TransactionLedger
    - notificationService : NotificationService
    --
    + createPayment(merchantId, amount, currency, method) : Payment
    + authorizePayment(paymentId) : AuthResult
    + capturePayment(paymentId) : CaptureResult
    + refundPayment(paymentId, amount) : RefundResult
    + getPaymentStatus(paymentId) : PaymentStatus
    + getPayment(paymentId) : Payment
}

note top of PaymentGateway #BBDEFB
    **STEP 1 - Start here.**
    "Merchant integrates with this one class.
    **Facade** hides: processor selection,
    provider communication, state management,
    ledger, and notifications."

    "Standard payment flow:
    createPayment() -> authorizePayment()
    -> capturePayment(). Or one-step:
    createPayment() with auto-capture."
    **Pattern: Facade | SRP, DIP**
end note


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 2: PAYMENT MODEL + STATE MACHINE
' ====================================================================
class Payment {
    - paymentId : String
    - merchantId : String
    - amount : double
    - currency : Currency
    - paymentMethod : PaymentMethodType
    - currentState : PaymentState
    - status : PaymentStatus
    - providerRef : String
    - createdAt : LocalDateTime
    - updatedAt : LocalDateTime
    - metadata : Map<String, String>
    - observers : List<PaymentObserver>
    --
    + authorize() : void
    + capture() : void
    + fail(reason) : void
    + refund() : void
    + cancel() : void
    + getAmount() : double
    + getStatus() : PaymentStatus
    + registerObserver(obs) : void
    + notifyObservers() : void
}

enum PaymentStatus {
    CREATED
    AUTHORIZED
    CAPTURED
    FAILED
    REFUNDED
    CANCELLED
    PARTIALLY_REFUNDED
}

enum Currency {
    INR
    USD
    EUR
    GBP
}

enum PaymentMethodType {
    CREDIT_CARD
    DEBIT_CARD
    UPI
    NET_BANKING
    WALLET
}

note top of Payment #FFCDD2
    **STEP 2 - Payment is the central object.**
    "Has amount, currency, method, status,
    and provider reference. Uses **State Pattern**
    (Step 3) and **Observer** (Step 7)."

    "PaymentStatus tracks lifecycle:
    CREATED -> AUTHORIZED -> CAPTURED
    AUTHORIZED -> CANCELLED
    CAPTURED -> REFUNDED
    Any -> FAILED"
end note

Payment --> PaymentStatus
Payment --> Currency
Payment --> PaymentMethodType


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 3: STATE PATTERN — Payment Lifecycle (KEY)
' ====================================================================
interface PaymentState <<State>> {
    + authorize(payment) : void
    + capture(payment) : void
    + fail(payment, reason) : void
    + refund(payment) : void
    + cancel(payment) : void
}

class CreatedState {
    + authorize(payment) : void
    + cancel(payment) : void
    + fail(payment, reason) : void
}

class AuthorizedState {
    + capture(payment) : void
    + cancel(payment) : void
    + fail(payment, reason) : void
}

class CapturedState {
    + refund(payment) : void
}

class FailedState {
    ' terminal — can retry with new payment
}

class RefundedState {
    ' terminal
}

class CancelledState {
    ' terminal
}

note bottom of PaymentState #FFCDD2
    **STEP 3 - Payment lifecycle. (KEY STEP)**
    "**State Pattern** — each state enforces
    what transitions are valid."

    "**CreatedState**: can authorize or cancel.
    **AuthorizedState**: can capture or cancel.
      (money reserved but not yet taken)
    **CapturedState**: can refund.
      (money transferred to merchant)
    **FailedState/CancelledState**: terminal.
    **RefundedState**: terminal."

    "Created -> Authorized -> Captured
    Authorized -> Cancelled (user changed mind)
    Captured -> Refunded (return/dispute)
    Any -> Failed (provider error)"

    "Key: AuthorizedState.authorize() throws
    — can't authorize twice. States enforce rules."
    **Pattern: State | SRP, OCP**
end note

PaymentState <|.. CreatedState
PaymentState <|.. AuthorizedState
PaymentState <|.. CapturedState
PaymentState <|.. FailedState
PaymentState <|.. RefundedState
PaymentState <|.. CancelledState
Payment --> PaymentState : delegates >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 4: PAYMENT PROVIDER — Strategy Pattern (KEY)
' ====================================================================
interface PaymentProvider <<Strategy>> {
    + authorize(request) : ProviderResponse
    + capture(providerRef, amount) : ProviderResponse
    + refund(providerRef, amount) : ProviderResponse
    + getStatus(providerRef) : ProviderResponse
    + supports(method) : bool
}

class RazorpayProvider {
    - apiKey : String
    - apiSecret : String
    --
    + authorize(request) : ProviderResponse
    + capture(providerRef, amount) : ProviderResponse
    + refund(providerRef, amount) : ProviderResponse
    + supports(method) : bool
}

class StripeProvider {
    - apiKey : String
    --
    + authorize(request) : ProviderResponse
    + capture(providerRef, amount) : ProviderResponse
    + refund(providerRef, amount) : ProviderResponse
    + supports(method) : bool
}

class PaytmProvider {
    - merchantId : String
    - merchantKey : String
    --
    + authorize(request) : ProviderResponse
    + capture(providerRef, amount) : ProviderResponse
    + refund(providerRef, amount) : ProviderResponse
    + supports(method) : bool
}

class ProviderResponse {
    - success : bool
    - providerRef : String
    - errorCode : String
    - errorMessage : String
    - rawResponse : String
}

note bottom of PaymentProvider #FFE0B2
    **STEP 4 - Which provider? (KEY STEP)**
    "**Strategy Pattern** — payment provider
    is pluggable. All implement same interface."

    "**RazorpayProvider**: India (UPI, cards, NB).
    **StripeProvider**: global (cards, wallets).
    **PaytmProvider**: India (wallet, UPI)."

    "supports(UPI)=true for Razorpay, false for
    Stripe. Provider selection uses this."

    "Add PhonePeProvider? One new class.
    Gateway unchanged."
    **Pattern: Strategy | OCP, DIP, LSP**
end note

PaymentProvider <|.. RazorpayProvider
PaymentProvider <|.. StripeProvider
PaymentProvider <|.. PaytmProvider
PaymentProvider --> ProviderResponse : returns >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 5: PROVIDER SELECTOR — Routing Logic
' ====================================================================
interface ProviderSelector <<Strategy>> {
    + selectProvider(payment) : PaymentProvider
}

class MethodBasedSelector {
    - providerMap : Map<PaymentMethodType, PaymentProvider>
    --
    + selectProvider(payment) : PaymentProvider
}

class CostBasedSelector {
    - providerCosts : Map<PaymentProvider, double>
    --
    + selectProvider(payment) : PaymentProvider
}

class FailoverSelector {
    - primary : PaymentProvider
    - fallback : PaymentProvider
    --
    + selectProvider(payment) : PaymentProvider
}

note bottom of ProviderSelector #FFE0B2
    **STEP 5 - Route to the right provider.**
    "Multiple providers. Which one for this payment?"

    "**Strategy Pattern** — routing is pluggable.
    **MethodBased**: UPI -> Razorpay, Cards -> Stripe.
    **CostBased**: pick cheapest transaction fee.
    **Failover**: try primary, if down use fallback."

    "Merchant can configure their preferred routing."
    **Pattern: Strategy | OCP, DIP**
end note

ProviderSelector <|.. MethodBasedSelector
ProviderSelector <|.. CostBasedSelector
ProviderSelector <|.. FailoverSelector
ProviderSelector --> PaymentProvider : selects >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 6: PAYMENT PROCESSOR — Orchestrates the Flow
' ====================================================================
class PaymentProcessor {
    - providerSelector : ProviderSelector
    - retryPolicy : RetryPolicy
    --
    + processAuthorization(payment) : AuthResult
    + processCapture(payment) : CaptureResult
    + processRefund(payment, amount) : RefundResult
}

class AuthResult {
    - success : bool
    - providerRef : String
    - errorMessage : String
}

class CaptureResult {
    - success : bool
    - capturedAmount : double
}

class RefundResult {
    - success : bool
    - refundedAmount : double
    - refundId : String
}

interface RetryPolicy <<Strategy>> {
    + shouldRetry(attempt, error) : bool
    + getDelayMs(attempt) : long
}

class ExponentialBackoffRetry {
    - maxRetries : int
    --
    + shouldRetry(attempt, error) : bool
    + getDelayMs(attempt) : long
}

class NoRetry {
    + shouldRetry(attempt, error) : bool
    + getDelayMs(attempt) : long
}

note bottom of PaymentProcessor #D1C4E9
    **STEP 6 - Orchestrates the flow.**
    "processAuthorization(payment):
    1. providerSelector.selectProvider(payment)
    2. provider.authorize(request)
    3. If success: payment.authorize()
       (state: CREATED -> AUTHORIZED)
    4. If fail: retryPolicy.shouldRetry()?
       Yes -> retry. No -> payment.fail()."

    "Same pattern for capture and refund.
    Retry via **Strategy** — ExponentialBackoff
    or NoRetry."
    **Pattern: Orchestrator | SRP**
end note

PaymentProcessor --> ProviderSelector : uses >
PaymentProcessor --> RetryPolicy : uses >
RetryPolicy <|.. ExponentialBackoffRetry
RetryPolicy <|.. NoRetry
PaymentGateway --> PaymentProcessor


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 7: OBSERVER — Notifications + Ledger
' ====================================================================
interface PaymentObserver <<Observer>> {
    + onPaymentEvent(payment, event) : void
}

class WebhookNotifier {
    - webhookUrl : String
    --
    + onPaymentEvent(payment, event) : void
}

class LedgerObserver {
    - ledger : TransactionLedger
    --
    + onPaymentEvent(payment, event) : void
}

class AuditLogObserver {
    --
    + onPaymentEvent(payment, event) : void
}

class FraudCheckObserver {
    --
    + onPaymentEvent(payment, event) : void
}

class TransactionLedger {
    - entries : Map<String, List<LedgerEntry>>
    --
    + record(paymentId, entry) : void
    + getEntries(paymentId) : List<LedgerEntry>
    + getMerchantBalance(merchantId) : double
}

class LedgerEntry {
    - type : LedgerEntryType
    - amount : double
    - timestamp : LocalDateTime
    - description : String
}

enum LedgerEntryType {
    AUTHORIZATION
    CAPTURE
    REFUND
    FEE
    SETTLEMENT
}

note bottom of PaymentObserver #B2EBF2
    **STEP 7 - React to payment events.**
    "On every state change, Payment calls
    notifyObservers(). **Observer Pattern**:"

    "**WebhookNotifier**: POSTs event to merchant's
    webhook URL ('payment.captured' with details).
    **LedgerObserver**: records debit/credit in
    double-entry ledger.
    **AuditLogObserver**: compliance trail.
    **FraudCheckObserver**: flags suspicious patterns."
    **Pattern: Observer | OCP, SRP**
end note

PaymentObserver <|.. WebhookNotifier
PaymentObserver <|.. LedgerObserver
PaymentObserver <|.. AuditLogObserver
PaymentObserver <|.. FraudCheckObserver
Payment --> PaymentObserver : notifies >
LedgerObserver --> TransactionLedger : writes to >
TransactionLedger *-- LedgerEntry
LedgerEntry --> LedgerEntryType
PaymentGateway --> TransactionLedger


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 8: MERCHANT + IDEMPOTENCY
' ====================================================================
class Merchant {
    - merchantId : String
    - name : String
    - apiKey : String
    - webhookUrl : String
    - enabledMethods : Set<PaymentMethodType>
    --
    + getMerchantId() : String
    + getWebhookUrl() : String
    + isMethodEnabled(method) : bool
}

class MerchantRegistry {
    - merchants : Map<String, Merchant>
    --
    + getMerchant(merchantId) : Merchant
    + registerMerchant(merchant) : void
    + authenticate(apiKey) : Merchant
}

class IdempotencyManager {
    - keys : Map<String, Payment>
    --
    + checkIdempotency(key) : Payment
    + register(key, payment) : void
}

note bottom of IdempotencyManager #C8E6C9
    **STEP 8 - Production concerns.**
    "**Merchant**: has API key, webhook URL,
    and enabled payment methods."

    "**IdempotencyManager**: prevents duplicate
    payments. If same idempotency key is sent
    twice, returns the original Payment instead
    of creating a new one. Critical for retries."
end note

PaymentGateway --> MerchantRegistry
PaymentGateway --> IdempotencyManager
MerchantRegistry o--> Merchant


' ====================================================================
'  WRAP UP
' ====================================================================
note as WRAPUP #FFFDE7
    **WRAP UP:** "Merchant calls createPayment(Rs 500, UPI).
    Gateway authenticates merchant, checks idempotency.
    PaymentProcessor selects Razorpay via **ProviderSelector**
    (**Strategy**). Razorpay authorizes (CREATED->AUTHORIZED via
    **State Pattern**). Merchant calls capturePayment()
    (AUTHORIZED->CAPTURED). **Observer** chain: WebhookNotifier
    POSTs to merchant, LedgerObserver records capture,
    AuditLog logs, FraudCheck scans."

    "5 patterns: **Facade**, **State** (payment lifecycle),
    **Strategy** (x3: provider, selector, retry),
    **Observer** (webhook, ledger, audit, fraud)."
end note


' ====================================================================
'  LEGEND
' ====================================================================
legend bottom
    |= Step |= What Happens |= Pattern |= SOLID |
    | 1 | Merchant calls PaymentGateway.createPayment() | Facade | SRP, DIP |
    | 2 | Payment: amount, currency, method, status, provider ref | -- | SRP |
    | 3 | Created -> Authorized -> Captured / Cancelled / Failed / Refunded | State | SRP, OCP |
    | 4 | Razorpay / Stripe / Paytm — all implement PaymentProvider | Strategy (provider) | OCP, DIP, LSP |
    | 5 | MethodBased / CostBased / Failover routing | Strategy (selector) | OCP, DIP |
    | 6 | Processor orchestrates: select provider -> call -> retry -> update state | Orchestrator | SRP |
    | 7 | Webhook, Ledger, AuditLog, FraudCheck all notified | Observer | OCP, SRP |
    | 8 | Merchant auth, idempotency key prevents duplicate payments | -- | Safety |
    |  |  |  |  |
    | **Auth + Capture** = Steps 3-6 | **Notify** = Step 7 | **Safety** = Step 8 (idempotency) |  |
endlegend

@enduml
